\section{Conclusion and future work}\label{sec:conclusion}
In this paper, a detailed analysis has been presented for the
synchronization of complex dynamical networks with impulsive
coupling. By utilizing the new concept of \textit{average impulsive
interval}, a \textit{unified} synchronization criterion is derived
for directed impulsive dynamical networks, which takes into account
two types of impulses \textit{simultaneously}. According to
theoretical analysis and numerical examples, our result has been
proved to be less conservative. Moreover, simulations are given to
confirm that the result can be applied to large-scale impulsive
dynamical networks.

In this paper, the impulsive strength is assumed to be invariable.
However, in reality, the strength of impulsive signal can be
different at different instants. Therefore, it would be of great
interest to study unified synchronization criterion for networks
with time-varying impulsive strength. Some good results have been
obtained in this issue
(\cite{guanzh2005ieeetac1058}\cite{guanzh2006ijbc229}). Moreover,
unified synchronization criterion for impulsive networks with
non-identical nodes will also be considered in the near future by
using the concept of tolerant error.

